## How to resolve

1. Open each conflicted file listed above.
2. Resolve every conflict-marker region thoughtfully, preserving the intent of
   BOTH the feature branch and `{{ target }}`. Never delete one side blindly.
3. Remove every `<<<<<<<`, `=======` and `>>>>>>>` marker line, so each file is
   left as valid, self-consistent content.

## Hard rules

- DO NOT run any git command. Ralph Workflow stages the resolved files and
  creates the merge commit itself. You only edit file contents. Git is denied
  to this session by the exec policy, so attempting it wastes the round.
- Do not commit, merge, rebase, abort, switch branches, or move any ref.
- Do not modify files that had no conflict, except as strictly required to make
  the resolved code consistent.
- A leftover conflict marker in ANY listed file REJECTS the whole resolution
  and aborts the merge. Ralph Workflow re-scans every listed path textually
  after you return; your own report is never the evidence.

## Completion contract

When every listed file is resolved and marker-free, call the
`declare_complete` MCP tool (`mcp__ralph__declare_complete`) with a short
summary of what you resolved.

Exiting cleanly WITHOUT calling `declare_complete` is treated as a FAILED
round, not as a resolution.
